Package object

Class Summary
Connection A connection object consists of two nodes and an Connection and is used as the basis of this program to solve the algorithms, it also contains a unique ID to identify if needed.
Edge An edge object consists of the edge weight, as well as an edge ID.
Graph A Graph is an array List of connects, as it is essentially a set of connections that are all joined.
Node Node objects consist of a label as well as co-ordinates and are used as part of connection objects to both get input and output of graphs and/or trees.
